      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Tricky. DELIBERATE PLOY (2) comes here off a solid debut win over this track and distance, settling just off the speed and coming away to win well. Didn't beat a whole lot there and no doubt this is tougher, but he maps well and should be able to improve a fair bit following that experience. YAMASHITA'S GOLD (4) has been thereabouts in three runs this time in without winning, in some handy races. He should get a nice run here and can break through. SHEZASMOKEY (6) ran well fresh at Moe in an easier race and has trialled since. Each-way. BATTLE OF THE ICE (1) resumes with upside, not far away at his only run last time in. Respecting from the inside gate.",
